SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 1642
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE OVERCAST.
4277H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 488, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to courthouse
construction or renovation projects.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 488, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 488.071, to read as follows:
488.071. 1. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, the
2 county commission of any county of the third classification may withhold and use up to
3 fifty percent of all court costs and court fees collected in such county for new courthouse
4 construction projects or renovation of an existing courthouse project.
5 2. No county shall use court costs and court fees withheld under subsection 1 of
6 this section for more than seven consecutive years per project.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

